## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="bc01c-102">Вы можете получить состояние звуковых входной механизма распознавания речи с <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.AudioState%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> и <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.AudioState%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> свойства.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="bc01c-102">You can obtain the audio input state of the speech recognition engine with the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.AudioState%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> and <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.AudioState%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> properties.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="bc01c-103"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.AudioStateChanged?displayProperty=nameWithType> И <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.AudioStateChanged?displayProperty=nameWithType> события вызываются, когда состояние меняется механизм распознавания речи входного аудио.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="bc01c-103">The <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.AudioStateChanged?displayProperty=nameWithType> and <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.AudioStateChanged?displayProperty=nameWithType> events are raised when the audio input state of a speech recognition engine changes.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="bc01c-104">Ниже приведен пример обработчика событий, который обрабатывает аудио с изменением состояния распознавателя речи.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="bc01c-104">The following example demonstrates an event handler that handles the changing audio state of a speech recognizer.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
  
private SpeechRecognitionEngine sre;  
  
// Initializes the speech recognition engine.  
private void Initialize()  
{  
  sre = new SpeechRecognitionEngine();  
  
  // Add a handler for the AudioStateChanged event.  
  sre.AudioStateChanged += new EventHandler<AudioStateChangedEventArgs>(sre_AudioStateChanged);  
  
  // Add other initialization code here.  
}  
  
  // Handle the AudioStateChanged event.  
  void sre_AudioStateChanged(object sender, AudioStateChangedEventArgs e)  
{  
  AudioState newState = e.AudioState;  
  
  // Handle event here.  
}  
  
```
